  {
    id: 'faq-2',
    title: 'Are there any age restrictions?',
    answer: 'All students from ages 5 and up are welcome.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-3',
    title: 'Where do we purchase an instrument, equipment and music? How will we know what to buy?',
    answer:
      'In your initial lesson, your teacher will determine and recommend the appropriate sized instrument for you. You will also be given a list of items to buy before your upcoming lesson.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-4',
    title: 'Will students have performance opportunities throughout the year?',
    answer:
      'Most definitely. Our music school organises bi-yearly student concerts and performance opportunities for well-prepared students of all levels, including beginners.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-5',
    title:
      'Do you prepare and help students apply for AMEB/ABRSM/Trinty exams? What about orchestral auditions or Eisteidffords for more advanced students?',
    answer:
      'We have been successfully preparing students for the above exams, auditions and competitions for over a decade. It is important to note that participation in the above is entirely optional.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-6',
    title: 'Where are lessons and rehearsals held? Do you do home visits?',
    answer: 'All classes are held on premises.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-7',
    title: 'What is the duration of each lesson?',
    answer:
      'Lessons are 30, 45 or 60 minutes long. The duration of each lesson is determined by the teacher and student.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-8',
    title: 'Can I change my lesson day and time?',
    answer:
      'You are automatically booked for the same day and time each week for the entirety of the school term. That is your personal lesson time and it isn’t subject to change until the following term. We have a small window during school holidays to make changes if possible.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-9',
    title: 'Can I book a one-off lesson?',
    answer:
      'Lessons are 30, 45 or 60 minutes long. The duration of each lesson is determined by the teacher and student.',
